verses.text_plain: And the Lord spake unto Moses in mount Sinai, saying,
verses.verse_html: 1And the Lord spake unto Moses in mount Sinai, saying,

verses.text_plain: Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye come into the land which I give you, then shall the land keep a sabbath unto the Lord.
verses.verse_html:
2Speak unto the children of Israel, and say unto them, When ye come into the land which I give you, then shall the land keep a sabbath unto the Lord. ▼
▼ keep: Heb. rest

verses.text_plain: Six years thou shalt sow thy field, and six years thou shalt prune thy vineyard, and gather in the fruit thereof;
verses.verse_html: 3Six years thou shalt sow thy field, and six years thou shalt prune thy vineyard, and gather in the fruit thereof;

verses.text_plain: But in the seventh year shall be a sabbath of rest unto the land, a sabbath for the Lord: thou shalt neither sow thy field, nor prune thy vineyard.
verses.verse_html: 4But in the seventh year shall be a sabbath of rest unto the land, a sabbath for the Lord: thou shalt neither sow thy field, nor prune thy vineyard.

verses.text_plain: That which groweth of its own accord of thy harvest thou shalt not reap, neither gather the grapes of thy vine undressed: for it is a year of rest unto the land.
verses.verse_html:
5That which groweth of its own accord of thy harvest thou shalt not reap, neither gather the grapes of thy vine undressed: for it is a year of rest unto the land. ▼
▼ of thy vine…: Heb. of thy separation

tokens.text: That which groweth of its own accord

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of thy vine…: Heb. of thy separation
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of thy vine…: Heb. of thy separation

verses.text_plain: And the sabbath of the land shall be meat for you; for thee, and for thy servant, and for thy maid, and for thy hired servant, and for thy stranger that sojourneth with thee,
verses.verse_html: 6And the sabbath of the land shall be meat for you; for thee, and for thy servant, and for thy maid, and for thy hired servant, and for thy stranger that sojourneth with thee,

tokens.text: for you; for thee, and for thy servant

verses.text_plain: And for thy cattle, and for the beast that are in thy land, shall all the increase thereof be meat.
verses.verse_html: 7And for thy cattle, and for the beast that are in thy land, shall all the increase thereof be meat.

verses.text_plain: And thou shalt number seven sabbaths of years unto thee, seven times seven years; and the space of the seven sabbaths of years shall be unto thee forty and nine years.
verses.verse_html: 8And thou shalt number seven sabbaths of years unto thee, seven times seven years; and the space of the seven sabbaths of years shall be unto thee forty and nine years.

verses.text_plain: Then shalt thou cause the trumpet of the jubile to sound on the tenth day of the seventh month, in the day of atonement shall ye make the trumpet sound throughout all your land.
verses.verse_html:
9Then shalt thou cause the trumpet of the jubile to sound on the tenth day of the seventh month, in the day of atonement shall ye make the trumpet sound throughout all your land. ▼
▼ of the jubile: Heb. loud of sound

tokens.text: Then shalt thou cause the trumpet

footnotes.body_text: ▼ of the jubile: Heb. loud of sound
footnotes.body_html: ▼ of the jubile: Heb. loud of sound

verses.text_plain: And ye shall hallow the fiftieth year, and proclaim liberty throughout all the land unto all the inhabitants thereof: it shall be a jubile unto you; and ye shall return every man unto his possession, and ye shall return every man unto his family.
verses.verse_html: 10And ye shall hallow the fiftieth year, and proclaim liberty throughout all the land unto all the inhabitants thereof: it shall be a jubile unto you; and ye shall return every man unto his possession, and ye shall return every man unto his family.

tokens.text: thereof: it shall be a jubile
unto you; and ye shall return

verses.text_plain: A jubile shall that fiftieth year be unto you: ye shall not sow, neither reap that which groweth of itself in it, nor gather the grapes in it of thy vine undressed.
verses.verse_html: 11A jubile shall that fiftieth year be unto you: ye shall not sow, neither reap that which groweth of itself in it, nor gather the grapes in it of thy vine undressed.

tokens.text: be unto you: ye shall not sow
of itself in it, nor gather
in it of thy vine undressed

verses.text_plain: For it is the jubile; it shall be holy unto you: ye shall eat the increase thereof out of the field.
verses.verse_html: 12For it is the jubile; it shall be holy unto you: ye shall eat the increase thereof out of the field.

verses.text_plain: In the year of this jubile ye shall return every man unto his possession.
verses.verse_html: 13In the year of this jubile ye shall return every man unto his possession.

verses.text_plain: And if thou sell ought unto thy neighbour, or buyest ought of thy neighbour’s hand, ye shall not oppress one another:
verses.verse_html: 14And if thou sell ought unto thy neighbour, or buyest ought of thy neighbour’s hand, ye shall not oppress one another:

verses.text_plain: According to the number of years after the jubile thou shalt buy of thy neighbour, and according unto the number of years of the fruits he shall sell unto thee:
verses.verse_html: 15According to the number of years after the jubile thou shalt buy of thy neighbour, and according unto the number of years of the fruits he shall sell unto thee:

verses.text_plain: According to the multitude of years thou shalt increase the price thereof, and according to the fewness of years thou shalt diminish the price of it: for according to the number of the years of the fruits doth he sell unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 16According to the multitude of years thou shalt increase the price thereof, and according to the fewness of years thou shalt diminish the price of it: for according to the number of the years of the fruits doth he sell unto thee.

verses.text_plain: Ye shall not therefore oppress one another; but thou shalt fear thy God: for I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 17Ye shall not therefore oppress one another; but thou shalt fear thy God: for I am the Lord your God.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore ye shall do my statutes, and keep my judgments, and do them; and ye shall dwell in the land in safety.
verses.verse_html: 18Wherefore ye shall do my statutes, and keep my judgments, and do them; and ye shall dwell in the land in safety.

verses.text_plain: And the land shall yield her fruit, and ye shall eat your fill, and dwell therein in safety.
verses.verse_html: 19And the land shall yield her fruit, and ye shall eat your fill, and dwell therein in safety.

verses.text_plain: And if ye shall say, What shall we eat the seventh year? behold, we shall not sow, nor gather in our increase:
verses.verse_html: 20And if ye shall say, What shall we eat the seventh year? behold, we shall not sow, nor gather in our increase:

verses.text_plain: Then I will command my blessing upon you in the sixth year, and it shall bring forth fruit for three years.
verses.verse_html: 21Then I will command my blessing upon you in the sixth year, and it shall bring forth fruit for three years.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall sow the eighth year, and eat yet of old fruit until the ninth year; until her fruits come in ye shall eat of the old store.
verses.verse_html: 22And ye shall sow the eighth year, and eat yet of old fruit until the ninth year; until her fruits come in ye shall eat of the old store.

verses.text_plain: The land shall not be sold for ever: for the land is mine; for ye are strangers and sojourners with me.
verses.verse_html:
23The land shall not be sold for ever: for the land is mine; for ye are strangers and sojourners with me. ▼
▼ for ever: or, to be quite cut off: Heb. for cutting off

footnotes.body_text: ▼ for ever: or, to be quite cut off: Heb. for cutting off
footnotes.body_html: ▼ for ever: or, to be quite cut off: Heb. for cutting off

verses.text_plain: And in all the land of your possession ye shall grant a redemption for the land.
verses.verse_html: 24And in all the land of your possession ye shall grant a redemption for the land.

verses.text_plain: If thy brother be waxen poor, and hath sold away some of his possession, and if any of his kin come to redeem it, then shall he redeem that which his brother sold.
verses.verse_html: 25If thy brother be waxen poor, and hath sold away some of his possession, and if any of his kin come to redeem it, then shall he redeem that which his brother sold.

tokens.text: and if any of his kin

verses.text_plain: And if the man have none to redeem it, and himself be able to redeem it;
verses.verse_html:
26And if the man have none to redeem it, and himself be able to redeem it; ▼
▼ himself…: Heb. his hand hath attained and found sufficiency

footnotes.body_text: ▼ himself…: Heb. his hand hath attained and found sufficiency
footnotes.body_html: ▼ himself…: Heb. his hand hath attained and found sufficiency

verses.text_plain: Then let him count the years of the sale thereof, and restore the overplus unto the man to whom he sold it; that he may return unto his possession.
verses.verse_html: 27Then let him count the years of the sale thereof, and restore the overplus unto the man to whom he sold it; that he may return unto his possession.

verses.text_plain: But if he be not able to restore it to him, then that which is sold shall remain in the hand of him that hath bought it until the year of jubile: and in the jubile it shall go out, and he shall return unto his possession.
verses.verse_html: 28But if he be not able to restore it to him, then that which is sold shall remain in the hand of him that hath bought it until the year of jubile: and in the jubile it shall go out, and he shall return unto his possession.

tokens.text: to him, then that which is sold

verses.text_plain: And if a man sell a dwelling house in a walled city, then he may redeem it within a whole year after it is sold; within a full year may he redeem it.
verses.verse_html: 29And if a man sell a dwelling house in a walled city, then he may redeem it within a whole year after it is sold; within a full year may he redeem it.

verses.text_plain: And if it be not redeemed within the space of a full year, then the house that is in the walled city shall be established for ever to him that bought it throughout his generations: it shall not go out in the jubile.
verses.verse_html: 30And if it be not redeemed within the space of a full year, then the house that is in the walled city shall be established for ever to him that bought it throughout his generations: it shall not go out in the jubile.

tokens.text: And if it be not redeemed

verses.text_plain: But the houses of the villages which have no wall round about them shall be counted as the fields of the country: they may be redeemed, and they shall go out in the jubile.
verses.verse_html:
31But the houses of the villages which have no wall round about them shall be counted as the fields of the country: they may be redeemed, and they shall go out in the jubile. ▼
▼ they may…: Heb. redemption belongeth unto it

footnotes.body_text: ▼ they may…: Heb. redemption belongeth unto it
footnotes.body_html: ▼ they may…: Heb. redemption belongeth unto it

verses.text_plain: Notwithstanding the cities of the Levites, and the houses of the cities of their possession, may the Levites redeem at any time.
verses.verse_html: 32Notwithstanding the cities of the Levites, and the houses of the cities of their possession, may the Levites redeem at any time.

verses.text_plain: And if a man purchase of the Levites, then the house that was sold, and the city of his possession, shall go out in the year of jubile: for the houses of the cities of the Levites are their possession among the children of Israel.
verses.verse_html:
33And if a man purchase of the Levites, then the house that was sold, and the city of his possession, shall go out in the year of jubile: for the houses of the cities of the Levites are their possession among the children of Israel. ▼
▼ a man…: or, one of the Levites redeem them

footnotes.body_text: ▼ a man…: or, one of the Levites redeem them
footnotes.body_html: ▼ a man…: or, one of the Levites redeem them

verses.text_plain: But the field of the suburbs of their cities may not be sold; for it is their perpetual possession.
verses.verse_html: 34But the field of the suburbs of their cities may not be sold; for it is their perpetual possession.

verses.text_plain: And if thy brother be waxen poor, and fallen in decay with thee; then thou shalt relieve him: yea, though he be a stranger, or a sojourner; that he may live with thee.
verses.verse_html:
35And if thy brother be waxen poor, and fallen in decay with thee; then thou shalt relieve him: yea, though he be a stranger, or a sojourner; that he may live with thee. ▼
▼ fallen…: Heb. his hand faileth
 , ▼
▼ relieve: Heb. strengthen

footnotes.body_html: ▼ fallen…: Heb. his hand faileth

verses.text_plain: Take thou no usury of him, or increase: but fear thy God; that thy brother may live with thee.
verses.verse_html: 36Take thou no usury of him, or increase: but fear thy God; that thy brother may live with thee.

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not give him thy money upon usury, nor lend him thy victuals for increase.
verses.verse_html: 37Thou shalt not give him thy money upon usury, nor lend him thy victuals for increase.

verses.text_plain: I am the Lord your God, which brought you forth out of the land of Egypt, to give you the land of Canaan, and to be your God.
verses.verse_html: 38I am the Lord your God, which brought you forth out of the land of Egypt, to give you the land of Canaan, and to be your God.

verses.text_plain: And if thy brother that dwelleth by thee be waxen poor, and be sold unto thee; thou shalt not compel him to serve as a bondservant:
verses.verse_html:
39And if thy brother that dwelleth by thee be waxen poor, and be sold unto thee; thou shalt not compel him to serve as a bondservant: ▼
▼ compel…: Heb. serve thyself with him with the service, etc

tokens.text: unto thee; thou shalt not compel

footnotes.body_text: ▼ compel…: Heb. serve thyself with him with the service, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ compel…: Heb. serve thyself with him with the service, etc

verses.text_plain: But as an hired servant, and as a sojourner, he shall be with thee, and shall serve thee unto the year of jubile:
verses.verse_html: 40But as an hired servant, and as a sojourner, he shall be with thee, and shall serve thee unto the year of jubile:

verses.text_plain: And then shall he depart from thee, both he and his children with him, and shall return unto his own family, and unto the possession of his fathers shall he return.
verses.verse_html: 41And then shall he depart from thee, both he and his children with him, and shall return unto his own family, and unto the possession of his fathers shall he return.

verses.text_plain: For they are my servants, which I brought forth out of the land of Egypt: they shall not be sold as bondmen.
verses.verse_html:
42For they are my servants, which I brought forth out of the land of Egypt: they shall not be sold as bondmen. ▼
▼ as…: Heb. with the sale of a bondman

footnotes.body_text: ▼ as…: Heb. with the sale of a bondman
footnotes.body_html: ▼ as…: Heb. with the sale of a bondman

verses.text_plain: Thou shalt not rule over him with rigour; but shalt fear thy God.
verses.verse_html: 43Thou shalt not rule over him with rigour; but shalt fear thy God.

verses.text_plain: Both thy bondmen, and thy bondmaids, which thou shalt have, shall be of the heathen that are round about you; of them shall ye buy bondmen and bondmaids.
verses.verse_html: 44Both thy bondmen, and thy bondmaids, which thou shalt have, shall be of the heathen that are round about you; of them shall ye buy bondmen and bondmaids.

tokens.text: you; of them shall ye buy

verses.text_plain: Moreover of the children of the strangers that do sojourn among you, of them shall ye buy, and of their families that are with you, which they begat in your land: and they shall be your possession.
verses.verse_html: 45Moreover of the children of the strangers that do sojourn among you, of them shall ye buy, and of their families that are with you, which they begat in your land: and they shall be your possession.

verses.text_plain: And ye shall take them as an inheritance for your children after you, to inherit them for a possession; they shall be your bondmen for ever: but over your brethren the children of Israel, ye shall not rule one over another with rigour.
verses.verse_html:
46And ye shall take them as an inheritance for your children after you, to inherit them for a possession; they shall be your bondmen for ever: but over your brethren the children of Israel, ye shall not rule one over another with rigour. ▼

verses.text_plain: And if a sojourner or stranger wax rich by thee, and thy brother that dwelleth by him wax poor, and sell himself unto the stranger or sojourner by thee, or to the stock of the stranger’s family:
verses.verse_html:
47And if a sojourner or stranger wax rich by thee, and thy brother that dwelleth by him wax poor, and sell himself unto the stranger or sojourner by thee, or to the stock of the stranger’s family: ▼

verses.text_plain: After that he is sold he may be redeemed again; one of his brethren may redeem him:
verses.verse_html: 48After that he is sold he may be redeemed again; one of his brethren may redeem him:

verses.text_plain: Either his uncle, or his uncle’s son, may redeem him, or any that is nigh of kin unto him of his family may redeem him; or if he be able, he may redeem himself.
verses.verse_html: 49Either his uncle, or his uncle’s son, may redeem him, or any that is nigh of kin unto him of his family may redeem him; or if he be able, he may redeem himself.

verses.text_plain: And he shall reckon with him that bought him from the year that he was sold to him unto the year of jubile: and the price of his sale shall be according unto the number of years, according to the time of an hired servant shall it be with him.
verses.verse_html: 50And he shall reckon with him that bought him from the year that he was sold to him unto the year of jubile: and the price of his sale shall be according unto the number of years, according to the time of an hired servant shall it be with him.

tokens.text: shall be according unto the number

verses.text_plain: If there be yet many years behind, according unto them he shall give again the price of his redemption out of the money that he was bought for.
verses.verse_html: 51If there be yet many years behind, according unto them he shall give again the price of his redemption out of the money that he was bought for.

tokens.text: unto them he shall give again

verses.text_plain: And if there remain but few years unto the year of jubile, then he shall count with him, and according unto his years shall he give him again the price of his redemption.
verses.verse_html: 52And if there remain but few years unto the year of jubile, then he shall count with him, and according unto his years shall he give him again the price of his redemption.

verses.text_plain: And as a yearly hired servant shall he be with him: and the other shall not rule with rigour over him in thy sight.
verses.verse_html: 53And as a yearly hired servant shall he be with him: and the other shall not rule with rigour over him in thy sight.

verses.text_plain: And if he be not redeemed in these years, then he shall go out in the year of jubile, both he, and his children with him.
verses.verse_html:
54And if he be not redeemed in these years, then he shall go out in the year of jubile, both he, and his children with him. ▼

verses.text_plain: For unto me the children of Israel are servants; they are my servants whom I brought forth out of the land of Egypt: I am the Lord your God.
verses.verse_html: 55For unto me the children of Israel are servants; they are my servants whom I brought forth out of the land of Egypt: I am the Lord your God.
